HandlerDict is a dictionary class representing a logging handler, primarily used in the LoggingConfig configuration dictionary to handle logging handlers. In the example below, a HandlerDict object is created with a "DEBUG" level and a "simple" formatter, then added to a LoggingConfig dictionary specifying the configuration for the logging system:

```python
from typing import Union
from automata_docs.core.utils import HandlerDict, LoggingConfig, RootDict

logging_handler = HandlerDict(level="DEBUG", formatter="simple")

logging_config: LoggingConfig = {
    "version": 1,
    "disable_existing_loggers": False,
    "formatters": {
        "simple": {
            "format": "%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s",
        },
    },
    "handlers": {"console": logging_handler},
    "root": RootDict(level="INFO", handlers=["console"]),
}
```
Note that HandlerDict is not intended for use as a standalone dictionary outside the context of LoggingConfig.

